5.1 The Involution θ(x) = −x as a Relational Gate
The Leech lattice VOA 𝑉_Λ carries an involution 

     𝜃 : 𝑉_Λ → 𝑉_Λ,      𝜃(𝑥) = −𝑥. 

This involution is not merely a symmetry; it is a boundary operator 
that partitions the VOA into two relational sectors:

Untwisted fixed sector:

     𝑉_Λ^+ = { 𝑣 ∈ 𝑉_Λ : 𝜃(𝑣) = 𝑣 }

Twisted sector:

     𝑉_Λ^− = states with fractional moding induced by 𝜃

The Monster cannot act on 𝑉_Λ alone. It requires the fusion of 
these two sectors.

5.2 Why the Untwisted Lattice VOA Cannot Host the Monster
The automorphism group of the untwisted lattice VOA is:

     Aut (𝑉_Λ)=Co_1. 

This is already enormous, but it is not the Monster. The obstruction 
is structural:

     Co₁ preserves the even unimodular quadratic form of the lattice.
     Monster elements outside Co₁ do not preserve this form.
     Therefore, Monster symmetry cannot act on 𝑉_Λ without altering 
      the relational boundary conditions.

The Z₂ twist is the mechanism that breaks the pure lattice symmetry 
and expands it.

